<p><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/spacer.gif width=5><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/headers/current_affairs.gif><center><table width=100%><tr><td background=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/horizon_line.gif><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/spacer.gif height=16></td></tr></table><p><table Border=0 Bgcolor=#181818 Width=100%>
<tr><td colspan=2 Bgcolor=#000000 Align=center><font color=white size=+2>Raid Role.</font>
</td></tr><tr><td width=10% Bgcolor=#101010 Align=center Valign=top><table width=200><tr><td align=center><font size=-1><table><tr><td align=center><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_top.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_left.jpg><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/portraits/ZASHEE.jpg width="104" height="184"><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_right.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_bottom.jpg></td></tr></table>Legendary  ZASHEE IXI`BANE<br>Level 64 Druid<br><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_11.gif" title="Silver Order of Leadership"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_1.gif" title="Service Cross"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_6.gif" title="Order of Meritorious Service"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_16.gif" title="Service Star Cluster"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_7.gif" title="Star of Achievement"><br>Raid Leader<br><a style="text-decoration:none;" href="main.cgi?fetch=ZASHEE"><font size=-1 color="#DDDDDD">ZASHEE</font></a><font size=-1>'S LINEAGE</font><br><img src='http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/bio.gif' border=0></font></td></tr></table></td><td width=90% Valign=top><a href=main.cgi?followup=6&forum=9><p align=right><font color=#cccccc>Reply | </a><a href=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/guild-builder/call/main.cgi?action=messages&forum=9><font color=#cccccc>Return</a></p><br clear=all><p><i> Okay, I may not be the highest druid nin the guild, but I am the first to post anything here...<br><br> The reason I bacame a druid for exploration. Being able to see all the zones before I was even of level to be in them. In addition, the ability to solo at any givin time, and do as many as 4 at a single time.<br><br> Soloing is not easy, and after you get all the levels and exp, you find that at higher levels, you missed out on a lot... Beginning to view yourself as nothing more than a porter and someone to give them sow. Correct me if I am wrong.<br><br> As you begin to get into the 50+ levels, you start to realize there is a lot more involved than sow, buff, port. You start to split into several classes just to fill in positions that would be needed for that specific raid.<br><br> You are the guide, in most cases. As a druid, you should know the lay of the land to get your group safely to their destination. During this time, you are the leader. If you do not know the way, and you have ample time before the raid, go explore it, invis, sow, lev the some of the many spells that will help you with this task. That way, when it comes time, you will be prepared for the wandering group member that somehow got lost. If, on the other hand, you did not have a chance to do any exploring, ASK FOR HELP!!! you leading them, and not knowing where you are going, will not help anyone, there is always someone else that can help with a few directions. Might even be a group member that has been there before.<br><br> Buffing: check the levels of the other druids, find out what they have planned for buffing. If you have mana free buffs, let them know, it can save some down time before the mob gets pulled. Do a final check to make sure all have your buffs.<br><br> You ARE the backup healer. Watch for messages in the group you are in, if you see someone that needs a heal, do it. If you see the message halfway through that the cleric has the heals under control, without endangering the MA, then interuppt yours. If you see the clerics interrupted as well, get with the fast heals immediatly. Always make sure you have the mana for fast heals, just in case the cast time for CH just wont make it in time.<br><br> You can ALSO be nuker, not nearly a match for the wizard, but pretty close second. Nukes get a lot of argo,very fast, this can put you at the top of the list, so be sure to wait an additional 15-20% more than after the assist is called. Gateing type mobs need to be burned before they get the mana to gate. Most will begin to gate around 15-30% life. This cannot happen. On a raid, it is a team effort, if that mob gates, he will then begin to summon one by one, till the raid force is gone... Would you like to try to solo a mob that is strong enuff to take a raid force down? And the cost of coffins and time for rebuffs just does not justify screwin around while the task needs to be done.<br><br> Additional tasks: Druids have debuff dots/nukes. If it is not being done by a higher level, have them ready, just remember that they create a LOT of argo, and make sure the tank has sufficient control befor doing so. A good guideline would be an additional 10% after the assist is called. Also, the more dots you can lay on the mob, the better, if, at worst, all it does is eliminate the mob's regen, that can make all the difference.<br><br> At the end, when all is said and done, and it is time for all to go home... druids and wizards will be the last to leave, anyone that cannot gate needs a ride out... most of your casters have bound outside of the zone, they will need a ride as well. Dont forget to remind them to rebind at their preferred location when your gone. As with the rest of them, you should have been bound outside the zone. When the tells come, that someone that had gone LD during the raid is still over there and really needs to be gotten, be willing to go get them. Most people understand that this is something that just has to be done, and most have been in that position before.<br><br><br> I really hope that some of this helps. and it is not just a very long ramble... any suggestions are always appreciated and accepted.<br><br> Be safe, travel lite... and dont forget to nuke low level mobs to see how powerful you really are.<br><br><br clear=all></i><br></td></tr><tr><td>
